Pinus patula

   [1703.jpg]
   Authority Schlechtend. & Cham.
   Family Pinopsida:Pinaceae
   Synonyms
   Common names Mexican yellow pine, jelecote pine, patula pine, pinheiro
   de jelecote, pinheiro patula
   Editor
   Ecocrop code 1703

   Notes
   BRIEF DESCRIPTION A medium-sized, slender evergreen tree reaching a
   height of 20-30 m or even more. Usually with a straight and cylindrical
   bole, sometimes forked. USES The wood is used for light construction
   work, boxes, ceilings, joinery and flooring, and for paper production.
   KILLING T Moderately frost resistant. GROWING PERIOD Perennial. COMMON
   NAMES Patula pine, Spreading-leaved pine, Mixican weeping pine,
   Jelecote pine. FURTHER INF Patula pine is native to central and eastern
   Mexico, where it can be found at elevations from 1400 to 3200 m. It is
   also grown on New Zealand and in central Africa. The tree occur
   naturally within the latitudinal range of 18-20Â°N. Annual wood
   production potential is 15-40 m3/ha.

   Sources
   SOURCES (P. patula Schiede & Deppe subsp. patula)
   Webb D 1984 pp 223 [RAIN, TEMP, TEXT, PH, DRA, DEP, LIG, KTMP, USE]
   Edwards S 1984 pp 223
   INSPIRE species 140 [RAIN, TEMP, TEXT, PH, DRA, DEP, LIG, USE]
   Morandina R 1961 pp 132 [TEMP, RAIN]
   Soerianegara I 1993 pp 349 & 357 [USE]

